column1: #FORMAT=WebAnno TSV 3.2
#T_SP=webanno.custom.Referent|entity|infstat
#T_RL=webanno.custom.Coref|type|BT_webanno.custom.Referent
#Text=On some national competitions they have a B4 class .
#Text=Do you think those should be eligible ?
#Text=In terms of the international competition ?
#Text=Which sports have B4s ?
#Text=There 's a level down , it 's not used internationally , I think it 's only used for domestic competitions .
#Text=I know the UK uses it .
#Text=I think I ... A particular one .
#Text=For social reasons , that 's a great thing , but I think if it 's , yeah .
#Text=I do n't know if I would ...
#Text=I think socially to get more Paralympic athletes involved in the sport if they 've got a degenerative condition on that border then they should be allowed to compete but obviously ...
#Text=I do n't think they should be able to receive any medals at a national competition or anything like that .
#Text=So I was , after Beijing , I was able to fore-run races .
#Text=I was able to transition over to skiing even though at that stage I was n't eligible .
#Text=So that was great for us .
#Text=The IPC knew that my eyesight was going to get worse .
#Text=So I was able to fore-run races .
#Text=Which was a really good experience for us , when we did get to that level .
#Text=So I think , with the lack of numbers in Paralympic sport , more that you should encourage athletes and give them those opportunities , it 's a great thing .
#Text=But I guess it 's about the athletes realizing that you 're in it for the participation , and to grow as an athlete rather than to win medals .
#Text=I do n't think the system should be changed .
#Text=I think three classes is enough .
#Text=Where the B3 line is compared with a B4 is legally blind .
#Text=And I think that covers everything .
#Text=I think that 's the stage where you have low enough vision to be considered a Paralympic sport as opposed to I guess an able bodied athlete .
#Text=And that 's with all forms of like , with government pensions , with bus passes , all that sort of stuff , that the cut off line is legally blind , so I think that 's a good place to keep it .
#Text=Veering away from this , I remember watching the Melbourne Cup stuff on television , and there you were , I think you were wearing some hat or something .
#Text=Yeah , my friend 's a milliner .
#Text=They were real flowers , real orchids .
#Text=Are you basically a professional athlete who has enough money or sponsorship to do that sort of stuff ?
#Text=I was saying , there 's Jessica Gallagher !
#Text=She was in London !
#Text=That 's so cool !
#Text=There are two organizations that I 'm an ambassador for , and one of them is Vision Australia , who were a charity for the Melbourne Cup Carnival .
#Text=So as part of my ambassador role I was at the races helping them raise money .
#Text=And that involves media stuff , so that was the reason I was there .
#Text=I did n't get paid .
